<!-- ══ STARTUP IMPLICATIONS ══ -->
<div class="sec-head"><span class="sec-num">§06</span> Startup Implications</div>
<div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;">
  <div style="border:1.5px solid var(--ink);padding:1rem;background:var(--surface)">
    <div style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif;font-size:1.1rem;margin-bottom:.5rem;color:var(--green)">PRODUCT INSIGHT</div>
    <div style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--ink2);line-height:1.65">English speakers need stronger hasty-generalization coaching than German speakers. A localized coaching system is not optional — cultural argumentation styles differ enough to require separate training curricula. First product market: German schools (stronger structural argumentation culture).</div>
